Reasoning: The paper deals with the task of hand gesture-to-gesture translation, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel approach using a Generative Adversarial Network (GAN) and introduces two new losses, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (AI). The paper also deals with the issue of self-occlusions, which is related to graphics (GR) and multimedia (MM).
